docs.abstract: Vaping-related lung illnesses have been on the rise, and federal and state health departments are investigating the risks.
docs.snippet: Vaping-related lung illnesses have been on the rise, and federal and state health departments are investigating the risks.
docs.lead_paragraph: Walmart said on Friday that it would stop selling e-cigarettes at its stores in the United States,  dealing a new blow to the vaping industry as concerns mount over the health risks of the products and their soaring popularity among teenagers.

headline.main: Walmart to End Sales of E-Cigarettes as Vaping Concerns Mount
headline.print_headline: At Walmart, Vaping Items Going Away

byline.original: By David Yaffe-Bellany, Michael Corkery and Sheila Kaplan

docs.abstract: The Labor Department set the income threshold at $35,500, the first increase since 2004 but a weaker standard than the Obama administration proposed.
docs.snippet: The Labor Department set the income threshold at $35,500, the first increase since 2004 but a weaker standard than the Obama administration proposed.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Labor Department announced Tuesday that it had finalized a rule expanding overtime pay eligibility to up to 1.3 million workers.

headline.main: Overtime Pay Eligibility Is Widened in New Federal Rule
headline.print_headline: Overtime Eligibility Widened, but Short of Obama Level

docs.abstract: The S.E.C. has prosecuted 50 percent more Ponzi cases in the last 10 years. Those scams cost their victims $31 billion.
docs.snippet: The S.E.C. has prosecuted 50 percent more Ponzi cases in the last 10 years. Those scams cost their victims $31 billion.
docs.lead_paragraph: It has been more than 10 years since Bernard L. Madoff was caught running the biggest Ponzi scheme in history, a case that became a cautionary tale for investors and a call to action for regulators. The Securities and Exchange Commission made changes in its enforcement division to better detect fraud, established specialized teams and even revamped its system for handling tips from the public.

headline.main: In the Decade Since Madoff, Ponzi Schemers Try New Tactics
headline.print_headline: Ponzi Tactics Changing In the Post-Madoff Era

docs.abstract: The company, which began as a comedy website, has branched out to podcasts and feature films, including “Between Two Ferns: The Movie,” which debuts on Netflix on Friday.
docs.snippet: The company, which began as a comedy website, has branched out to podcasts and feature films, including “Between Two Ferns: The Movie,” which debuts on Netflix on Friday.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Will Ferrell found himself seated next to Michelle Obama at a White House Christmas party in 2010 when she leaned over and began quoting lines from Funny or Die’s “The Landlord” — the viral video featuring a 2-year-old girl shouting profanities at Mr. Ferrell for not turning in his rent money on time.

headline.main: Funny or Die Finds New Life in the Streaming Era
headline.print_headline: Comedy Brand Recalibrates for Life in the Streaming Age

docs.abstract: The automaker has reportedly offered to create a battery factory in the same Ohio area. But the work would pay far less than the shuttered plant.
docs.snippet: The automaker has reportedly offered to create a battery factory in the same Ohio area. But the work would pay far less than the shuttered plant.
docs.lead_paragraph: In its negotiations with the striking United Auto Workers union, General Motors has put a seemingly tantalizing offer on the table: It has proposed building a new plant in Ohio to produce batteries for some of the one million electric cars it hopes to sell globally by 2026.

headline.main: Lordstown Plant Is Idle, but It Hovers Over G.M. Strike Talks
headline.print_headline: Ohio Plant Is Idle, but It Hovers Over G.M. Strike Talks

docs.abstract: Volkswagen’s top two leaders were charged by German prosecutors with failing to inform investors of the U.S. investigation into emissions cheating.
docs.snippet: Volkswagen’s top two leaders were charged by German prosecutors with failing to inform investors of the U.S. investigation into emissions cheating.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Volkswagen was supposed to turn the corner this year from the shadow of a costly diesel emissions scandal, with a new emphasis on electric vehicles, a new logo and a new commitment to ethical behavior.

headline.main: VW Executives and Ex-C.E.O. Are Charged With Market Manipulation
headline.print_headline: VW’s Leaders Accused Of Manipulating Market

docs.abstract: Unemployment is near a 50-year low and jobs openings exceed applicants. That’s causing a high-stakes scramble for talent in the public sector.
docs.snippet: Unemployment is near a 50-year low and jobs openings exceed applicants. That’s causing a high-stakes scramble for talent in the public sector.
docs.lead_paragraph: Peanut season is nearly upon South Carolina and, like governments across the country, the state has been scrambling to hire.

headline.main: A Hot Job Market Is Causing Labor Pains for State Governments
headline.print_headline: With Market Hot for Jobs, States Strain

docs.abstract: As the long bull market shows signs of fatigue, some industry analysts are starting to ask: What will become of all the upstart brands when the economy sours?
docs.snippet: As the long bull market shows signs of fatigue, some industry analysts are starting to ask: What will become of all the upstart brands when the economy sours?
docs.lead_paragraph: Moxy and Motto. Autograph, Avid and Alila. Edition, Element and Even. Big hotel management companies have been acquiring or inventing new brands at a dizzying pace in the past several years.

headline.main: Hotels Have Piled On the Brands. In a Downturn, That Could Be a Problem.
headline.print_headline: Saturating the Hotel Market, Brand by Brand

docs.abstract: Hackers have been targeting regular people and celebrities with the attack. Last week, it was used to hijack the Twitter account of Twitter’s C.E.O.
docs.snippet: Hackers have been targeting regular people and celebrities with the attack. Last week, it was used to hijack the Twitter account of Twitter’s C.E.O.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — When hackers took over the Twitter account of Twitter’s chief executive, Jack Dorsey, last week, they used an increasingly common and hard-to-stop technique that can give them complete access to a wide array of the most sensitive digital accounts, including social media, email and financial accounts.

headline.main: Hackers Hit Twitter C.E.O. Jack Dorsey in a ‘SIM Swap.’ You’re at Risk, Too.
headline.print_headline: A Dastardly Phone Hack That You Cannot Prevent

docs.abstract: Exercise manias like the Thighmaster and Tae Bo have all come and gone. Peloton is trying to defy that trend.
docs.snippet: Exercise manias like the Thighmaster and Tae Bo have all come and gone. Peloton is trying to defy that trend.
docs.lead_paragraph: As far as indoor cycling machines go, the $2,245 Peloton bike is nothing special. It has a sleek black and red frame. It has a big screen. It’s on Wi-Fi.

headline.main: Peloton Is a Phenomenon. Can It Last?
headline.print_headline: Racing Ahead Now, but Is It Another Fad?
